What do the scholars say of Buddhist literature? Have they got it in its
completeness? Assuredly not. Notwithstanding the 325 volumes of the
*Kanjur* and the *Tanjur* of the Northern Buddhists, each volume we are
told, "weighing from four to five pounds," nothing, in truth, is known
